{
  "texts": [
    "Second, they follow an isolated sign language recognition logic, where the translated sign language is a rigid one-to-one correspondence with spoken words.",
    "They overlook the grammatical conventions that are characteristic of authentic sign language communication.",
    "Moreover, many applications, such as the Auslan Signbank, 6 offer text-tovideo functionality based merely on simple database queries.",
    "This approach results in certain text vocabulary items being untraceable to their corresponding sign language gestures when these words are not indexed, despite having existing sign video equivalents.To this end, current endeavors remain experimental and lack the capacity to meet the challenges of practical application, both in terms of data diversity and methodological robustness.",
    "For instance, the HandTalk Appfoot_3 is aiming at helping hearing individuals learn American Sign Language (ASL) and Brazilian Sign Language (Libras) through demonstrations linked to English/British sentences."
  ]
}